President Biden has appointed four individuals to the U.S. AbilityOne Commission, which oversees the AbilityOne Program that provides employment opportunities for people who are blind or have significant disabilities. The appointees are Bryan Bashin, CEO of the Lighthouse for the Blind and Visually-Impaired in San Francisco; Christina Brandt, CEO of AtWork!; Gabe Cazares, Director of the Mayor's Office for People with Disabilities in Houston; and Chai Feldblum, a national expert in disability law and employment. These individuals bring extensive experience and expertise in the field of disability advocacy and employment.